00:26:43.610 --> 00:26:47.450
been easy for you to follow
this approach consistently?

00:26:47.450 --> 00:26:50.360
Has it been tested
over the years?

00:26:50.360 --> 00:26:53.780
Have there have been times where
you've questioned how you've

00:26:53.780 --> 00:26:56.164
thought about these things?

00:26:56.164 --> 00:26:57.830
FRANCOIS ROCHON: Yeah,
it's been tested.

00:26:57.830 --> 00:27:01.700
Because like I said, we have
to accept that we underperform

00:27:01.700 --> 00:27:02.960
one year out of the three.

00:27:02.960 --> 00:27:06.730
And you know, in the good
years, it's easy to say.

00:27:06.730 --> 00:27:10.240
But when those bad years
happen, it's really painful.

00:27:10.240 --> 00:27:14.000
And you know, when you
have some partners--

00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:16.670
well, the word you
use for clients--

00:27:16.670 --> 00:27:20.390
you have to explain to them,
well, why you have a bad year.

00:27:20.390 --> 00:27:22.050
