00:28:05.391 --> 00:28:06.390
this is a good approach.

00:28:06.390 --> 00:28:07.650
Maybe I want to try it.

00:28:07.650 --> 00:28:10.830
And you know, they could
have a couple of bad years

00:28:10.830 --> 00:28:11.710
to start off with.

00:28:11.710 --> 00:28:13.940
And what is your advice there?

00:28:16.804 --> 00:28:18.220
FRANCOIS ROCHON:
I think there's--

00:28:18.220 --> 00:28:21.180
patience, also, it's
important, of course.

00:28:21.180 --> 00:28:24.590
But I think there's a
quality behind patience,

00:28:24.590 --> 00:28:26.790
and it's humility.

00:28:26.790 --> 00:28:29.445
You have to accept that
you'll make some mistakes.

00:28:29.445 --> 00:28:32.080
And there's always things
that you can learn.

00:28:32.080 --> 00:28:35.610
And I would say that the
greatest quality of Warren

00:28:35.610 --> 00:28:37.700
Buffett is not
necessarily intelligence,

00:28:37.700 --> 00:28:38.640
it's the humility.

00:28:38.640 --> 00:28:40.950
I mean, he's the greatest
investor of all time.

00:28:40.950 --> 00:28:42.630
He's the greatest of all.

00:28:42.630 --> 00:28:45.390
But he's still
very humble, always

00:28:45.390 --> 00:28:47.410
looking to improve and learn.

00:28:47.410 --> 00:28:49.530
And I think that's
his greatest quality.

00:28:49.530 --> 00:28:56.660
He's 87 years old, and he's
still striving for new learning

00:28:56.660 --> 00:28:57.330
everyday.

00:28:57.330 --> 00:28:59.520
You always want to
learn new things

00:28:59.520 --> 00:29:00.910
and understand new things.

00:29:00.910 --> 00:29:05.910
And if you have
those qualities, I

00:29:05.910 --> 00:29:08.622
think you'll succeed in
almost anything you do.

00:29:08.622 --> 00:29:10.080
SPEAKER 1: That's
