00:29:19.930 --> 00:29:20.690
some points.

00:29:20.690 --> 00:29:22.570
SPEAKER 1: Yeah, selling, sure.

00:29:22.570 --> 00:29:24.120
Thank you.

00:29:24.120 --> 00:29:25.380
Yeah.

00:29:25.380 --> 00:29:27.840
So you do believe that
it's more than the IQ.

00:29:27.840 --> 00:29:29.700
It's the behavioral
traits, after a point,

00:29:29.700 --> 00:29:30.450
that are critical.

00:29:30.450 --> 00:29:31.366
FRANCOIS ROCHON: Yeah.

00:29:31.366 --> 00:29:33.150
SPEAKER 1: OK.

00:29:33.150 --> 00:29:37.500
So any advice to individual
investors, young investors

00:29:37.500 --> 00:29:40.500
who might not be professional
investors like yourself?

00:29:40.500 --> 00:29:42.650
What are some best practices
that one can adopt?

00:29:47.120 --> 00:29:50.400
FRANCOIS ROCHON: I think, first,
you have to look for a company

00:29:50.400 --> 00:29:51.600
that you can understand.

00:29:51.600 --> 00:29:53.790
Because there's many,
many companies out there.

00:29:53.790 --> 00:29:55.590
There's, you know,
thousands and thousands.

00:29:55.590 --> 00:30:00.210
And it's hard to really
understand all those companies.

00:30:00.210 --> 00:30:03.040
And some are just
very, very complicated.

00:30:03.040 --> 00:30:05.460
So you're trying
to play a hard game

00:30:05.460 --> 00:30:09.510
when you want to be able
to value every company.

00:30:09.510 --> 00:30:12.600
You play an easier game
when you're very selective,

00:30:12.600 --> 00:30:15.950
and you just go for the company
that you can understand.

00:30:15.950 --> 00:30:20.010
And it goes back to the
analogy of Ted Williams,

00:30:20.010 --> 00:30:22.350
that he wanted to wait
for the perfect pitch that

00:30:22.350 --> 00:30:25.050
was in the sweet spot zone.

00:30:25.050 --> 00:30:28.470
And I think that's the beautiful
thing about the stock market.

00:30:28.470 --> 00:30:30.680
And Warren Buffett said
that many, many years ago,

00:30:30.680 --> 00:30:33.630
that investing is the
greatest business of all,

00:30:33.630 --> 00:30:36.570
because that's the
one you can choose

00:30:36.570 --> 00:30:38.220
the ball you want to hit.

00:30:38.220 --> 00:30:41.400
So you have the luxury
of standing at the plate.

00:30:41.400 --> 00:30:43.470
And you know, we're waiting
for the perfect ball.

00:30:43.470 --> 00:30:45.100
There's no called strike.

00:30:45.100 --> 00:30:47.250
And that's, I think,
the most beautiful thing

00:30:47.250 --> 00:30:48.480
in the investment business.

00:30:48.480 --> 00:30:52.470
But at the same time, it's
a very competitive investing

00:30:52.470 --> 00:30:53.560
world.

00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:55.460
So there are some
disadvantages too.

00:30:55.460 --> 00:30:59.880
But if you have the right
behavior, the right approach,

00:30:59.880 --> 00:31:06.360
and you're very patient and very
selective, I think, in the end,

00:31:06.360 --> 00:31:07.342
you'll succeed.

